8 and its possible route from Venice to Paris between 1746 and 1792 investigated.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aRoland (Legendary character)vRomances. 4aChanson de Roland. 4aChâteauroux-Manuskript. 4aEdition. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / French.2bisacsh  aChanson de Roland.  aChâteauroux Version.  aEdition.  aHistory of the French Language.  aMedieval French Literature.1 aMoffat, Marjorie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Literary and Cultural Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023846408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015z978311074296108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2014z9783110370270oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831103731030 cprintz978311033961140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311033974140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110339741423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110339741/original  a978-3-11-023846-4  DGBA Backlist Literary and Cultural Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-074296-1  De Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyt